The course is aimed at MA students training to become language teachers. It provides students with an overview of the issues in the field of language acquisition, learning and teaching, with key theoretical studies in these areas and their application in language teaching practice.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course provides an overview of theoretical principles of language acquisition, learning and teaching, research into these areas and its influence on language teaching practices.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On successful completion of the course, the students will be able to 1. define terms and concepts related to language learning and teaching  2. describe the principles and uses of the Common European Framework of Reference for Languages  3. use the common reference levels to assess students' spoken and written language proficiency 4. describe principal language acquisition theories and relate them to general learning theories 5. list similarities and differences between first and second language acquisition 6. describe individual learner characteristics, learning styles and strategies  7. know the specific characteristics of language teaching methods and approaches 8. are informaed about the issues in the fields of foreign language acquisition, learning and teaching
